	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">No More WIndows 95 users? What is the Deal?</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=527682" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    &lt;blockquote&gt;<BR>
Since many of us can not get in the game tonight following the short 22 hour patch to luclin, we figured we would answer a few user question..<BR>
&lt;br&gt;<BR>
JJJordon writes...&lt;br&gt;<BR>
&lt;blockquote&gt;<BR>
&lt;font size=-1&gt;<BR>
With in the past 6 months I purchased Everquest with the Kunark Expansion pack.  On the box it says that system requirements are as follows:&lt;br&gt;<BR>
Windows 95/98/00&lt;br&gt;<BR>
Pent 200&lt;br&gt;<BR>
64 MB RAM&lt;br&gt;<BR>
Direct 3D or Glide Compliant excellerator card W/8mg RAM&lt;br&gt;<BR>
600 MB hard drive space&lt;br&gt;<BR>
28.8 + internet connection&lt;br&gt;<BR>
Directx compatible sound card&lt;br&gt;<BR>
2x CD ROM&lt;br&gt;<BR>
&lt;br&gt;<BR>
It says nothing in regard to haveing  a min of windows 98, it says nothing about them changing the play environment or system requirements. Is this legal?  I have already upgraded one system and purchased a new one in order to play this  game with my son.  My new system that I purchased less than a year ago is now not good enough to play.  The older system a PIII 350 is not good enough nor the new 8MB video card I purchased for the older computer.  My new system only has 16MB video card and only 124 mb of RAM.  How can they do this so that the original 3 continents of the game can no longer be played?&lt;br&gt;<BR>
  Is there a possiblity of a lawsuite here?<BR>
Thanks for your help.  I have cried half the day as I am not able to go out and buy another new system nor am I able to upgrade our existing sytems to comply with these new system requirements for an expansion, I do not even have.  I am on a limited income and very upset to say the least especially at Christmas time.&lt;br&gt;<BR>
Thanks EQ&lt;br&gt;<BR>
If you have any suggestions or if you too have this problem please e-mail me or post here.&lt;br&gt;<BR>
&lt;br&gt;<BR>
Fxersgal Shaman of 40 battles &lt;br&gt;<BR>
e-mail pinkshoe@2z.net<BR>
&lt;/font&gt;<BR>
&lt;/blockquote&gt;<BR>
<BR>
According to the Terms of Service that we all agree to when we start the game each time.  Basically, Verant has the right to do whatever they want, whenever they want with their game.  They may even cancel your account without reason, or shut the game down completely.  Changing the game also falls under that classification<BR>
&lt;/blockquote&gt;<BR>

		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
