				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				hello friends =)<BR>
<BR>
just as a quick point of perspective, EQ is part of the tech world, meaning as time goes on, it will be better than it was before (example - i had bought a computer system in january and by the time it got to me, there was already something much better.  its to be expected...) being an online game, it has the opportunity to do something that most of the games gathering dust on your shelf does not -- it gets upgraded, with new attributes.  (you might by the next series for a regular game, or the expansion, but after you pass it a couple times, its back in the pile with all the other old games.)  that is what makes the game interesting.. if not to you, then possibly to most of the friends that you have in it.<BR>
<BR>
such a thing does not come without a price -- which is why EQ has to be down for patches, especially when theyre bringing out something as major as a new expansion.  sure, you might not have wanted some thing that they had done, but when looking at the whole picture, you appreciate the new things that make everquest different.<BR>
<BR>
in a week, the problems youre experiencing will be fixed, it wont be so choppy, and you can log on fine again.<BR>
<BR>
also, when dealing with anything in the tech business, its to be expected that something that youre going to need to upgrade your system every few years (whether it be just parts of it, or the whole thing).  why?  because the technology that are coming out now wont work on what was good a few years back.  same thing goes for everquest... but remember, you can still play without the new expansion.  or you can play without its new graphics, if you were to buy luclin.  there are always options.<BR>
<BR>
just be patient while they work the bugs out. read a book, do the project youve been procrastinating over, go kiss the girlfriend/boyfriend you keep neglecting for the game, or take your kids to a movie =)  there has to be something to do while the patches are being implimented, while problems are being fixed.  but that doesnt mean that EQ is rendered unplayable.<BR>
<BR>
and remember!  happy holidays ^_^<BR>
<BR>
zanira kagasan of the nameless<BR>

