IT'S CHRISTMAS for God's sake and you are making me ashamed to be part of this human race...the man has a child that plays EQ with him, he has a character that he's put tremendous time into, and he doesn't know how to fix his system.  He's ASKING for help and all I see are people being a bunch of s*%theads.<BR>
<BR>
But remember, what goes around comes around...and to those of you who are being douchebags...well guess what?  I wouldn't piss on you if you were on fire, and I'm sure there are plenty of people who know you in RL that feel the same way, because an online schmuck is most likely a RL schmuck.  I would bet a year's salary that you have no empowerment in your real lives...that's why you would make such mean and insensitive remarks to someone that has done nothing harmful to anyone...he was just asking for advice and looking for EMPATHY...probably a foreign word to you unsympathetic sociopaths.<BR>
<BR>
As for liability...Verant DOES have a responsibility to recall any software packaging that has outdated information on it.  Otherwise it's false advertising.  What that boils down to as far as a legal settlement...not much...a refund of the software at most, and it would have to be a class action lawsuit.  It would also only include people who bought the software after Verant announced the new OS requirements, because that would be the time at which Verant would be obligated to remove all outdated packaging from the market.<BR>
<BR>
Should this gentleman upgrade if he can?  Yes, he should at least try to get Windows 98 if he wants to continue playing the old world.  Does he have a valid complaint?  Not legally, but he does have a right to be upset and disappointed, and to ask his fellow gamers for support, sympathy, and ADVICE as to how to correct his dilemma.<BR>
<BR>
The fact that he's not technologically the most up to date or savvy person in the world doesn't mean he should be treated with anything less than respect and compassion.  <BR>
<BR>
The hatred and anger in these posts makes my skin crawl.  The United States is at war to erradicate people that have no value for other human beings, and my god, I've just seen how much of it actually exists WITHIN my country.  If we can't be kind or tolerant to our own fellow Americans, then what is it we're fighting for?
