			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I am torn on this. What is the lesser of 2 evils here? Verant is trying to beat the competition with better gameplay and graphics. In return, they are requiring that a newer version of Windows and Directx be utilized to do so. The best case scenerio is that they will patch it to run Win 95 and a lower Directx since 8.1 isn't supported by Win95. Do you know how much lag this will cause for those of you on Win95? With out getting into computer geek specifics, You will be running a framerate that will be so slow that it isn't even worth playing the game. Those of you that have been on a raid with a modem will know what I am talking about. Not only will you be choppy as hell, you will have to get used to a LD state. The only way to remedy this is to take out the new enhancements. (I.e. scale down new zones and no new charectar models). Luclin requires that the Vah Shir be running on a highly textured mode and it can't be turned off. Any time you encounter a Vah Shir you will be moving with the quickness of a snail if you can even see them. Yesterday, there was a lvl 16 Vah Shir Beastlord in one of the new zones...point being that they will be in the old world soon enough thanks to large guilds. Most people have a newer version of Windows and Directx 8.1 is a free download. It makes since to upgrade the requirements to have a more visually pleasing game. I may be out of the loop, but you are talking approx. 10% of people at best that still use Win 95. You have to appeal to the numbers. Verant is within full legal rights to shut down the game at anytime if they so desire. You won't get a refund for your time or software in this case. Changing specs certainly won't hold water considering that Win95 is approaching being 7 years old. People that own Win 3x can make the same argument for other games. Noone complained when Kunark and Velious required 128 MB of RAM. Certainly there were those that still had 32 and 64 MB at that time.<BR>
<BR>
On the sympathetic side, I know the attachment that people get to their charectars. It sucks that you are not able to log into the game and enjoy it. Not everyone has the $ to upgrade, but I will say that you can't swing a dead cat without hitting someone that has Win98. It was issued with boxes of Tide detergent in my city. Ask someone. Upgrade to Win98 and download the newer Directx. Viola, you can play. You aren't required to buy the expansion. Maybe that is something for future consideration when $ is more readily available. Just my perspective...
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
	<tr>
			<td nowrap bgcolor="#808080" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_silver.gif">	
			<a href="/US_Admin.asp?mode=edit&amp;id=529530"><img border="0" src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif"></a>
			</font>
			<font face="Verdana" size="1"><b>
			Submited by:&nbsp;<a href="mailto:">HannibalX</a></font> 
