	</tr>
	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				The problem is that Windows 95 does not support DirectX8 which Everquest now requires for all versions of EQ, not just Luclin. Don't feel too alone, however because many users with otherwise acceptable systems but with certain video cards are being dropped,too. The word (not from Verant)is any card with less than 16 Megs is basically dropped, although some people say they are still playing with 8 meg cards so we have to wait and see. A lot of people with AMD chips are having problems, too. I think Verant got a little too enthusiastic when they upped the specs for the latest revision as a lot of people are being left behind. Zones that normally have over 50 people at a time now have less than 25. I don't know how long this can last before EQ becomes unprofitible to run due to lack of customers. Why is anyone still using Win 95 anyway? I started using that on my 486 and I got rid of it with my Pentium 150.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
